# No Upstream OpenClaw Source Edits

Do not edit upstream OpenClaw source code for Rumi work.

- Never modify files under `/home/kenny/openclaw/src/`.
- Do not add source patches, tests, or runtime changes to the OpenClaw checkout as a way to customize Rumi.
- If runtime behavior needs changing, first look for a plugin hook and implement it as Rumi-owned code outside upstream source, preferably under `workspace/plugins/` and mirrored into the live workspace.
- Prompt, cron configuration, Rumi workspace behavior files, docs, templates, and plugins are allowed.
- If no plugin/config/prompt approach can solve the issue, document the limitation and ask Kenny before proposing an upstream fork or patch branch.
